Added oracle bone script, but with an indication that someone carved it recently. How do you like dem apples? Oh, and your heading when you leave the islet is irrelevant. If you arrive at the islet from location X, when you leave (generally speaking, and subject to some not-fully-understood qualifications as indicated in the test log), you return to location X regardless of your vector of approach to the islet or your vector of departure from the islet. Fr'instance, if you arrived at the islet from Duluth, Minnesota (by traveling more or less eastward), then when you leave the island, if you keep going eastward you will eventually hit the Upper Peninsula just as if you had visited a non-anomalous rock during the journey.





