If spikebrennan approves, some suggested test logs:

Six identical amphibious drones carried to the island by boat, one from each of the six known access points. Drones roped together into a single jury-rigged unit and programmed to travel out of the SCP's known range and return. Combined drones exit as normal from Finland location. Stocktake confirms rope was brought to SCP-908 from Finnish access point.

Previous test is repeated with six new drones and six identical lengths of rope, one of each brought in via each point of access. Combined drones exit SCP's known range and all remote contact is lost. After 24 minutes, contact is re-established via satellite link. The drones have reappeared at [EXPUNGED], a location not previously known to be related to SCP-908 phenomena. GIS analysis suggests the point of emergence is the point on earth that is the shortest distance from all six SCP-908 access points.







